      "text": "**Niklas Luhmann**: Here, I think, language is not quite up to par with what should be said.  We need to bring the [[Language]] back into line with our [[Intention]]s. So I would answer yes and no. On the one hand, everything that can be seen or said takes place in the world, and they are always, in this sense, statements about the world. But just not about the unity of the world or about that which can never be left.\n\n\n"
